==English==
===Etymology===
Named for German physician and physicist [[w:Hermann Von Helmholtz|Hermann Ludwig Ferdinand von Helmholtz]].

===Noun===
'''Helmholtz [[resonator]]'''
{{wikipediapar|acoustics}}
#A container with an open [[hole]] or [[neck]] containing a [[column]] of [[compressible]] [[fluid]] ([[gas]]) and frequently used to [[attenuate]] a certain [[frequency]], as to eliminate [[noise]].

